Market-Based Rate Tariff
1. Availability Seller makes electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available under this tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below.
2. Rates All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller.
3. Seller Category Seller is a Category 2 Seller in the Northwest Region, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a)(3). Seller is a Category 1 Seller in all other Regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a)(2).
4. Compliance with Commission Regulations Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
5. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority Seller has received waiver of: Subparts B and C of Part 35, except sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41; Part 101, with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects; and Part 141, except sections 141.14 and 141.15; and received blanket approval under Part 34. Bakeoven Solar, LLC, Docket No. ER22-2173-000 (unpublished letter order).
6. Ancillary Services
PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc.
New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc.
California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. Seller is authorized to transact at market-based rates in the Energy Imbalance Market administered by the CAISO. Avangrid Renewables, LLC, et al., 182 FERC 61,193 (March 24, 2023).
MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO.
Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. ("SPP") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP.
Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.

ARTICLE 4 MANAGEMENT OF COMMON FACILITIES 4.1 Administrative Owner. Bakeoven shall be the Administrative Owner, subject to Bakeovens right to resign as Administrative Owner and a right of any Owner whose Project is of a nameplate MW capacity larger than the Bakeoven Solar Project to step in and replace Bakeoven as the Administrative Owner. If Bakeoven (or any other entity) resigns as Administrative Owner, a successor Administrative Owner shall be selected by the Owners Committee. In addition, any Owner may call for a vote for removal of Administrative Owner for cause, which cause would include negligence that has a material adverse effect on the operation or maintenance of the Common Facilities; provided, however, that any vote for removal of Administrative Owner for cause shall exclude the Administrative Owner that is the subject of the vote. Consistent with the requirements of each Owners interconnection agreement, BPA will be notified, in writing by the Owners Committee, of any changes to the Administrative Owner within thirty (30) calendar days of a new Administrative Owner having been selected by the Owners Committee. 4.2 Powers and Duties of Administrative Owner. The Administrative Owner shall, as agent of and on behalf of each of the Owners: (a) Operate and maintain (or provide for the operation and maintenance by a qualified third party) the Common Facilities, and maintain the Shared Premises (including all roads located thereon and any other portions of the Shared Premises upon which any Common Facilities are located), in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice, applicable laws, the terms of the Shared Real Property Documents, applicable interconnection agreements to which an Owner is a party, and commercially reasonable terms included in any insurance policies covering the Shared Premises upon which any Common Facilities are located and of which the Administrative Owner has received notice. In connection with such operation and maintenance, the Administrative Owner is authorized [REDACTED]; (b) Prepare annual budgets and budget amendments as required with respect to the Common Facilities, and present such budgets and budget amendments for review and approval by the Owners Committee; (c) Maintain up-to-date books and records related to the Common Facilities in accordance with generally acceptable accounting practices applicable to the electric utility industry and make such books and records available to each of the Owners upon the request of such Owner during the Administrative Owners regular business hours; (d) Procure policies of insurance pursuant to Section 7.1; (e) Perform, in accordance with Prudent Industry Practice, such other duties as may be specified by the Owners Committee; (f) Execute such contracts and other documents as are necessary or appropriate to carry out the duties enumerated in Sections 4.2(a) through 4.2(e); (g) Upon the request of any Owner, promptly provide to such Owner a statement, in such detail as may be reasonably requested by such Owner, of the amounts payable or reimbursable by such Owner pursuant to Section 4.4; (h) Review any proposal by an Owner to interconnect generation facilities [REDACTED]. Each Owner agrees to indemnify and hold the Administrative Owner harmless, and waives any claim against the Administrative Owner, for any action taken in good faith pursuant to this Section 4.2(h); (i) Serve as the primary point of contact with BPA for required notices and/or all communications required for the day-to-day operation, regulatory requirements of the Common Facilities, and the coordination of the operation of [REDACTED]; (j) Serve as the primary point of contact with FERC for required notices and filings under the Federal Power Act; and

4.3 Authorized Expenditures. To the extent included in an annual budget or a budget amendment approved and effective pursuant to Sections 5.7 through 5.9 of this Agreement, as well as any additional cost incurred by the Administrative Owner and reimbursable under this Agreement, including all Shared Expenses, each of the Owners shall reimburse to the Administrative Owner an amount proportionate to its Sharing Ratio [REDACTED], of (i) the salaries, wages and related indirect and overhead costs properly allocable to the Common Facilities for the Administrative Owners personnel who perform the duties and obligations of the Administrative Owner pursuant to this Agreement; (ii) the reasonable payments by the Administrative Owner to third parties related to or in connection with the carrying out of the duties and obligations of the Administrative Owner pursuant to this Agreement; and (iii) the fixed (i.e. not revenue-related) portion of any payments pursuant to the Shared Real Property Documents (the Authorized Expenditures). The Administrative Owner will not be entitled to recovery with respect to any indirect costs or payments (including pursuant to any judgment, decree, injunction, order or decision by any governmental authority) incurred or owing by the Administrative Owner as a result of or in connection with any mistake, action, inaction or omission constituting gross negligence, fraud or willful or wanton misconduct by the Administrative Owner. 4.4 Reimbursement of Approved Costs. The invoicing and payment of any reimbursement pursuant to Section 4.3 shall be as follows: (a) The Administrative Owner shall provide each Owner with an invoice no later than the tenth (10th) day of each month for Authorized Expenditures pursuant to Section 4.3 incurred during the previous month. The Administrative Owner shall promptly provide to each Owner such receipts, documents and other information in connection with each such statement as such Owner may reasonably request. ARTICLE 5 OWNERS COMMITTEE 5.1 Establishment of Committee; Voting. There is hereby established an Owners Committee to take all actions with respect to the Common Facilities, except as otherwise granted to the Administrative Owner pursuant to Article 4, and to take all other actions that all of the Owners may, from time to time, agree in writing that the Owners Committee is authorized to take in connection with the ownership (as applicable), rebuilding, operation, maintenance, repair, replacement and removal of the Common Facilities and the improvement and maintenance of the Shared Premises, or any portion thereof. Each Owner shall be entitled to appoint two (2) members to the Owners Committee, provided that no Owner shall be entitled to appoint or maintain a member on the Owners Committee unless that Owner has commenced operation of its Project and is using the Gen-Tie Line to transmit the output of its Project. The total number of members on the Owners Committee shall be equal to the product of two (2) times the number of Owners, unless unanimously agreed by the parties. Each member of the Owners Committee shall be entitled to cast one (1) vote. Each member of the Owners Committee shall have the right to cast such vote with respect to any decision, approval or other action to be made by the Owners Committee pursuant to this Agreement. If an Owners Committee member participating in a meeting of the Owners Committee does not vote either in favor of or against any matter subject to a decision, approval or other action of the Owners Committee pursuant to this Agreement, such member shall be deemed to have voted against it. Each decision, approval, or other action by the Owners Committee must be unanimous. A matter shall be deemed approved by the Owners Committee only if it shall have been approved by all of the votes of the Owners regardless of whether such Owners or their representative members on the Owners Committee are in attendance at the meeting. Consistent with each Owners interconnection agreement, BPA will be notified of any decision (A) to remove from service permanently or otherwise to dispose of the Gen-Tie Line, or (B) to make any capital expenditure for the purpose of increasing the Full Capacity of the Gen-Tie Line within thirty (30) calendar days of the Owners Committee approval. 5.2 Appointment of Members; Alternates. The members of the Owners Committee, as well as alternate members who may represent their respective Owners in the absence of the regular member, are identified on Exhibit E to this Agreement. Any Owner (or its successors and assigns, acting collectively) may change its Owners Committee member by giving written notice of such change to each other Owner, and upon receipt of such notice the Owners shall revise Exhibit E to this Agreement accordingly. Any Owner (or its successors and assigns, acting collectively), by giving written notice to each other Owner, may, for purposes of any decision, approval or other action to be made by the Owners Committee pursuant to this Agreement, appoint an alternate or alternates to serve on the Owners Committee in the place of, and to cast the vote of, the regular Owners Committee member appointed by such Owner. 5.3 Meetings. The Owners Committee shall meet regularly, but not less often than once each year, at such time and place as may be agreed upon by the members of the Owners Committee, and the Owners Committee shall meet at such other times and places as may be requested by any Owners Committee member by written notice to each other Owners Committee member at least thirty (30) days prior to such meeting. Members of the Owners Committee may participate in such meetings in person or by means of conference telephone calls or similar communications during which all persons participating in the meeting can hear each other. Participation in a meeting by means of conference telephone calls or similar communications shall be deemed to constitute presence in person at the meeting. Failure by any Owners Committee member to attend any annual or special meeting of the Owners Committee for which notice was properly given under this Section 5.3 shall not invalidate such meeting or any decisions, approvals or other actions taken at such meeting, and the non-attending member shall be deemed to have been present for purposes of a quorum and to have voted in favor of any matter subject to a vote by the Owners Committee at such meeting. 5.4 Decisions by Written Action. Any decisions, approvals and other actions that may be taken at a meeting of the Owners Committee may be taken without a meeting if all Owners Committee members consent thereto in writing. The Owners Committee may, by the unanimous vote of the members of the Owners Committee, adopt written procedures for review or approval of matters or for the taking of other actions concerning the Common Facilities. 5.5 Subcommittees. The Owners Committee may appoint such subcommittees as it deems necessary or appropriate and, by the unanimous vote of all of the members of the Owners Committee, may delegate approval authority to such subcommittees with respect to matters concerning the Common Facilities. Members of a subcommittee are not required to otherwise be a member of the Owners Committee. 5.6 Budgets. The Owners Committee shall have the authority to review and approve or amend the annual budgets and budget amendments prepared by the Administrative Owner pursuant to Section 4.2(b). If for any reason the Owners Committee does not approve an annual budget prior to the end of the eleventh (11th) month of the preceding operating year, the budget for such preceding operating year shall apply to operating year, subject to an increase or decrease in such budget to reflect the change in the GDPIPD for all goods and services during the twelve (12) month period ending with the tenth (10th) month of such preceding operating year. The Administrative Owner shall have the right but not the duty to proceed with an item that has been disapproved as provided in this Article, if the Administrative Owner determines in its reasonable judgment that such action is required to avoid an imminent threat of loss of life or property or is required to avoid an imminent threat of interruption of service over the Gen-Tie Line; provided, however, that if the Administrative Owner takes such action on a disapproved item and if the determination made in any subsequent review of the decision is that the item was not consistent with Prudent Industry Practice, then the Administrative Owner shall individually compensate the disapproving Owners for all of the net increase in cost or other financial impact of such action to the extent that it is inconsistent with what the reviewers determined would under such circumstances have met such test. 5.8 Tax Election. The Parties acknowledge and agree that (a) they shall seek acceptance by the FERC of this Agreement under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act; (b) any subsequent amendments to this Agreement that, pursuant to Section 205 of the Federal Power Act and FERC precedent thereunder, are required to be filed at FERC, must be accepted by FERC, and the effectiveness of such amendments will be contingent on such FERC acceptance; (c) changes in ownership contemplated by this Agreement may be subject to prior FERC approval pursuant to Section 203 of the Federal Power Act; and (d) disconnections or terminations contemplated by this Agreement may require prior FERC approval under the Federal Power Act. This Agreement shall become effective as of the date on which any required FERC or other entity with regulatory jurisdiction has approved, accepted for filing or permitted to become effective this Agreement without change or new condition (except for any change or new condition that is acceptable to each Owner). 13.4 Removal of Common Facilities from Service. When all of the Owners direct the Administrative Owner to permanently remove the Common Facilities from service, the Administrative Owner shall dispose of the Common Facilities, or of such part of the Common Facilities, as the case may be, being removed from service. After deducting all costs of disposing of the Common Facilities, or of such part of the Common Facilities, as the case may be, including the cost of removing all structures and disposing of the debris and meeting all requirements of applicable law, the Administrative Owner shall distribute to each Owner a percentage of net proceeds from such disposition equal to the ratio of its Ownership Interest to the Ownership Interest of all Owners. In the event such costs of disposing of the Common Facilities, or of part of the Common Facilities, as the case may be, pursuant to this Section 13.4, exceed the amount of the proceeds from the disposition of the Common Facilities or such part of the Common Facilities, each Owner shall pay a portion of excess costs related to the disposition of the Common Facilities or of such part of the Common Facilities, as the case may be, as such excess costs are incurred, equal to its Sharing Ratio. Administrative Owner will notify BPA of any removal of Common Facilities from service thirty (30) calendar days prior to the removal date. The terms of this Section 13.4 shall survive the termination of this Agreement. 13.5 No Abandonment; Termination; Withdrawal. (a) No act or failure to act on the part of any Owner shall be deemed to constitute an abandonment of the Ownership Interest of such Owner, except in accordance with Section 13.5(b)(iii). The Term of this Agreement shall terminate, except for terms that expressly survive the termination of this Agreement, upon the first to occur of: (i) a single Owner becoming the owner of the entire ownership interest in all of the Common Facilities after the occurrence of the first Sharing Effective Date, or (ii) the mutual agreement of all the Owners. This Agreement shall only terminate or be terminated as provided in this Section 13.5. (b) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Agreement, any Owner may elect to surrender its Ownership Interest and withdraw from this Agreement, but only with the consent of all of the Owners. The withdrawing Owner shall convey its Ownership Interest and assign its rights hereunder to the remaining Owner or Owners and, thereupon, the withdrawing Owner shall cease to have any right, title or interest in the Common Facilities or its Ownership Interest; provided that: (A) the withdrawing Owner executes and delivers all instruments of transfer as may be necessary or appropriate to effect (and that do effect) the conveyance of its Ownership Interest and assignment of its rights hereunder to, and which are reasonably satisfactory to, the remaining Owner or Owners, (B) such assignment and conveyance is accompanied by an assignment by the withdrawing Owner to the remaining Owner or Owners of all its rights under this Agreement and (C) an encumbered Ownership Interest may only be surrendered with the written consent of each secured party that holds a security interest in such Ownership Interest and a release of such secured party's security interest therein. No surrender of an Owner's Ownership Interest shall relieve the withdrawing Owner of any of its obligations under any agreement (including this Agreement and the obligation to pay its share of the Shared Expenses through the effective date of such surrender), unless expressly provided for in this Agreement, or agreed in a writing among the Owners. After the Sharing Effective Date, in addition to the obligations of the withdrawing Owner set forth herein and in the event an Owner desires to decommission and abandon its Project, and the Ownership Interest of such Owner is not accepted or the obligations under this Agreement of the withdrawing Owner are not assumed by another Owner in writing, the withdrawing Owner shall, upon notice to the other Owners of its intent to abandon its Project, be responsible for its proportionate share (as determined by such Owner's Ownership Interest as of the date notice of intent to abandon and decommission its Project is given to the other Owners) of the costs and expenses of the removal and wind-up of the Common Facilities and the restoration of the Shared Premises as required by the Shared Real Property Documents (collectively, the Withdrawal Costs). The Administrative Owner shall administer the calculation, collection, and distribution of the Withdrawal Costs, as follows (provided, however, that if the Administrative Owner is the withdrawing Owner, then the non-withdrawing Owner(s) shall have the rights and perform the obligations of the Administrative Owner under this Section 13.5): (i) The Administrative Owner shall calculate the Withdrawal Costs and shall provide written notice of same to the withdrawing Owner within forty-five (45) days after the Administrative Owner has received notice of Owner's intent to abandon its Project. (ii) The withdrawing Owner shall, within thirty (30) days of the receipt of the written notice of the Withdrawal Costs, pay the Withdrawal Costs to the Administrative Owner. The Withdrawal Costs shall be maintained by the Administrative Owner in a reserve account and used by the Administrative Owner for removal of the Common Facilities and the restoration of the Shared Premises when same becomes necessary. (iii) Upon any failure to pay the Withdrawal Costs constituting a default hereunder, the applicable Owner shall automatically forfeit all of its Ownership Interest hereunder to the other Owners and shall immediately cease and desist from the use of the Common Facilities. The withdrawing Owner further irrevocably appoints the Administrative Owner as its true and lawful attorney, with full power of substitution, for the sole use and benefit of the remaining Owners, but at the withdrawing Owner's expense, to the extent permitted by law to exercise, at any time and from time to time while the surrendering Owner's default has occurred and is continuing, the power to sell, transfer, assign or otherwise deal in or with the Ownership Interest of the withdrawing Owner or the proceeds thereof, as fully and effectually as if the Administrative Owner were the absolute owner thereof, provided that the Administrative Owner shall give to the withdrawing Owner not less than ten (10) days prior written notice of the time and place of a sale or other intended transfer or disposition of any of such Ownership Interest. Any Ownership Interest of the withdrawing Owner transferred or surrendered to the other Owners shall be allocated based on the Ownership Interests as recalculated in accordance with Section 2.2 after giving effect to such withdrawal, unless Bakeoven is no longer an Owner, in which case, such allocation shall be on a pro rata basis in accordance with each remaining Owner's Ownership Interest. 13.6 Unavoidable Delays. If any Party is delayed, hindered in or prevented from performing any act required under this Agreement by reason of strikes, lockouts, labor troubles, inability to procure materials, failure of power, restrictive governmental laws or regulations, natural disasters, war, terrorism, civil strife or other violence, the affected Party, upon giving notice to the other Party, shall be excused from performing the act (except payment of consideration) for the period of the delay. The affected Party shall use its reasonable efforts to avoid or remove the causes of nonperformance and shall continue performance whenever the causes for nonperformance are removed. 13.7 Run with the Land. The Parties hereby agree that all of the covenants, consents and agreements contained in this Agreement touch and concern the real estate described in this Agreement and are expressly intended to, and shall, to the extent allowed by law, be covenants running with the land and shall be binding and a burden upon said real estate and each Partys present or future estate or interest therein and upon each of the Parties, their respective successors and assigns as holders of an estate or interest in such real estate (including any lender or other person acquiring title from any such person upon foreclosure or by deed in lieu of foreclosure), and shall benefit the Parties and their respective successors and assigns and the real estate and any present or future holder of an estate or interest therein. To the extent any of the provisions of this Agreement are not enforceable as covenants running with the land, they shall be enforceable as equitable servitudes. 13.8 Certifications. Each Party shall, upon not less than ten (10) days prior written notice from time to time given by any other Party or by any existing or proposed lender, assignee, subgrantee or equity investor with respect to a Party (each, a Requesting Party), execute, acknowledge and deliver to the Requesting Party a written statement (a) certifying that the Grants and this Agreement are unmodified and in full force and effect (or, if modified, stating the nature of such modification and certifying that the Grants and this Agreement, as so modified, are in full force and effect), and (b) certifying that there are not, to the nonrequesting Partys knowledge, any uncured defaults hereunder, or describing with particularity each such uncured default if any are claimed. Any such statements may be conclusively relied upon by the Requesting Party. The failure of the nonrequesting Party to deliver any such statement within such time shall be conclusive upon such nonrequesting Party that (i) the Grants and this Agreement are in full force and effect and have not been modified and (ii) there are no uncured defaults hereunder. 13.9 Partition Waiver. The Owners agree that neither the Common Facilities nor the Shared Premises are suitable for partition. Accordingly, each Owner irrevocably waives any and all rights that it may have under applicable law to maintain any action, suit or claim for partition of all or any part of the Common Facilities. In the event that any Owner is an entity that distributes its interest in the Common Facilities and this Agreement to its members, shareholders, partners or owners voluntarily, in the course of dissolution or by operation of law, such distribution shall comply with all requirements of Section 13.4 of this Agreement, the distributees shall become Owners under this Agreement and each distributee shall be bound by the terms of this Agreement, including the waiver of any partition rights. 13.10 Entire Agreement/Amendments. This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement of the Parties with regard to its subject matter. This Agreement and the consents and other rights created by it shall not be modified or amended except in a writing signed by the Parties. 13.11 Further Assurances. The Parties agree to cooperate in executing any additional agreements or amendments reasonably needed by the Parties for their business purposes so long as they do not adversely affect the rights of the other Parties or violate the terms and spirit of this Agreement. 13.12 Choice of Law. This Agreement shall be deemed made and prepared and shall be construed and interpreted in accordance with the internal laws of the State of Oregon, without regard to principles of conflicts of law thereof that may require the application of the law of another jurisdiction. 13.13 Time of Essence. Time is of the essence with regard to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. 13.14 Partial Invalidity. Should any provision of this Agreement be held, in a final and unappealable decision by a court of competent jurisdiction, to be either invalid, void or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall remain in full force and effect, unimpaired by the holding. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, the Parties agree that in no event shall the Term be for longer periods than the longest periods permitted by applicable law. 13.15 Approvals. No approval required by this Agreement shall be unreasonably withheld or delayed. Unless a longer or shorter time is specified, all approvals required of either Party shall be given or refused in writing within ten (10) Business Days after receipt of the request for approval. Any delay of a requested approval longer than ten (10) Business Days shall be deemed an approval. Approvals shall not be unreasonably withheld except in instances where this Agreement specifically permits a Party to act in its sole discretion. 13.16 As-Is Condition. The Grants are granted and conveyed to each Subsequent Party subject to the present or future condition of the Shared Premises and AS-IS, WHERE-IS, with all faults, and each Subsequent Party hereby accepts the Grants and such Shared Premises in such condition and on such basis. Each Subsequent Party acknowledges that for purposes of this Agreement, neither Bakeoven nor any of its representatives or agents has made any representation or warranty as to the suitability of the Shared Premises or any portion thereof for the conduct of operations or for any other purpose. 13.17 Cooperation. Each Party shall reasonably support and cooperate with each other Party in the conduct of its operations and the exercise of its rights hereunder, and in carrying out and otherwise giving full force and effect to the purpose and intent of this Agreement, including in a Partys efforts to obtain from any governmental authority or any other Person any permit, entitlement, approval, authorization or other rights necessary or convenient in connection with its operations and/or the exercise of its rights hereunder; and each Party shall, without demanding additional consideration therefor, promptly execute, and, if appropriate, cause to be acknowledged and recorded, any map, application, document or instrument that is reasonably requested by any other Party or any governmental authority in connection therewith. 13.18 Attornment. If any other Person shall succeed to all of a Partys interests in the Shared Premises, this Agreement shall continue in full force and effect as a direct agreement between the then owner of such Partys interests in the Shared Premises and the other Party, upon and subject to all of the terms, covenants and conditions herein for the remaining balance of the term hereof, and the other Party does hereby attorn to such new holder, such attornment to be effective and self-operating without the execution of any further instruments. 13.19 No Third Party Beneficiaries. Except with respect to the rights of Lenders as stated above, the covenants contained herein are made solely for the benefit of the Parties hereto, and shall not be construed as benefiting any Person that is not a Party to this Agreement. 13.20 Entire Agreement; Multiple Counterparts. This Agreement, including the Exhibits and Schedules attached hereto (all of which are incorporated herein by this reference), contains the entire agreement between the Parties hereto in connection with any matter mentioned or contemplated herein, and all prior or contemporaneous proposals, agreements, understandings and representations, whether oral or written, are merged herein and superseded hereby. This Agreement may be executed in multiple counterparts, all of which shall constitute one and the same Agreement.
